class Solution {
    public int latestTimeCatchTheBus(int[] buses, int[] passengers, int capacity) {
        Arrays.sort(buses);
        Arrays.sort(passengers);
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        while (i < buses.length && j < passengers.length) {
            if (passengers[j] <= buses[i]) {
                j++;
                if (j % capacity == 0) i++;
            } else {
                i++;
            }
        }
        int latest = (i < buses.length) ? buses[i] : buses[buses.length - 1];
        while (j > 0 && passengers[j - 1] == latest) {
            j--;
            latest--;
        }
        return latest;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n + m log m)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Sort buses and passengers arrays, then iterate through both to simulate the boarding process. The latest time to catch a bus is determined by checking if there's an available seat on the last bus or the bus that is about to depart. If a passenger arrives at the same time as the latest possible arrival, decrement the latest time until it's no longer the same as a passenger's arrival time.
